body:
The bot will emit 'login' but after just spams 4-8 times:

DID NOT PARSE THE WHOLE THING!
DID NOT PARSE THE WHOLE THING!
DID NOT PARSE THE WHOLE THING!
DID NOT PARSE THE WHOLE THING!
(Sometimes after a few minutes it does some more)

What a great error. I don't know what is emitting it. I've tried searching it up in minecraft-protocol or mineflayer on git to see if it could find in code where it was added but I can't find anything. 'Login' is emitted but 'Spawn' is not. I recieve no errors from the 'err' event.

comment_data.body: What server are you using ? I'm not getting these errors...
Woops, that's a node-minecraft-protocol debug message I forgot to remove ^^' https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/blob/master/src/protocol.js#L1575
Yeah but it shouldn't happen, isn't it ?

@rom1504 yup, it probably means @demipixel is connecting to a server running the wrong version. Either that, or there's a bug in the protocol, but that seems unlikely to me, I checked almost everything...

I am attempting to connect to a 1.8 server (is that the wrong version?). The two things that happen are either THAT or:

return entity.username.toLowerCase() === filter.toLowerCase();
TypeError: Cannot call method 'toLowerCase' of undefined

So usually it either can't find an entity's username or it just can't parse some of the data...

@demipixel sorry for the late reply,l was gone most of the week-end. Could you set the "NODE_DEBUG" environment variable to mc-proto before launching the script, and pastebin the output ? This will enable node-minecraft-protocol's debug outputs, which should help me debug the issue
Also about the username problem : I think it may have been fixed by one of the last commits, so don't forget to git pull before you try again.
You should git pull the mineflayer repo, lots of updates. I think that issue has been fixed recently.

@roblabla http://hastebin.com/ibafizohox.vbs

I forked but I've been doing 'git fetch upstream/master' then merging but it says it's already up-to-date.
@demipixel I think this is the same problem as #213

title: Guys... We didn't parse.
